OL,3,CWill Labour lose its grip on power in
OL,4,Cthe Welsh election?
OL,6,FWith Labour behind in the polls, there
OL,7,Fis a growing sense of a major shift in
OL,8,FWelsh politics ahead of the Senedd
OL,9,Felection, reports Rhys Williams
OL,11,FThe Heads of the Valleys road slices
OL,12,Fthrough some of the most politically
OL,13,Fimportant communities in Britain.
OL,15,FFrom Tredegar to Neath and beyond,
OL,16,Fthese towns and villages haven't just
OL,17,Freturned Labour members for
OL,18,Fgenerations but helped to build the
OL,19,Fmovement itself.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/19
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,310,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30902
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F309A1776708665
OL,3,CWill Labour lose its grip on power in
OL,4,Cthe Welsh election?
OL,6,FIt was in Merthyr Tydfil and Aberdare
OL,7,Fthat the party's first member and
OL,8,Fleader, Keir Hardie, broke through.
OL,10,FWhile in Tredegar, Aneurin Bevan rose
OL,11,Ffrom the son of a coal miner to become
OL,12,Fone of the most consequential Labour
OL,13,Fcabinet ministers in the party's
OL,14,Fhistory.
OL,16,FThe careers of figures like Michael
OL,17,FFoot and Neil Kinnock further cemented
OL,18,Fthe south Wales valleys as the
OL,19,Fsymbolic heartland of Labour politics.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/19
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,310,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30903
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F309A1776708665
OL,3,CWill Labour lose its grip on power in
OL,4,Cthe Welsh election?
OL,6,FFor more than a century, that bond has
OL,7,Fappeared unbreakable.
OL,9,FBut with Labour consistently falling
OL,10,Fbehind in the polls in Wales, there is
OL,11,Fa growing sense that something deeper
OL,12,Fmay be shifting.
OL,14,FTravelling the route from Tredegar
OL,15,Fwest towards Neath, the long-term
OL,16,Feconomic changes that have reshaped
OL,17,Fdaily life are difficult to ignore.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/19
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,310,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30904
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F309A1776708665
OL,3,CWill Labour lose its grip on power in
OL,4,Cthe Welsh election?
OL,6,FRoads that once carried workers to
OL,7,Fpits, factories, and steelworks now
OL,8,Fmore often take people out of the
OL,9,Fregion towards jobs elsewhere.
OL,11,FIn Maesteg, former Labour council
OL,12,Fleader Jeff Jones stood with me next
OL,13,Fto the site of what was once one of
OL,14,Fthe Llynfi Valley's biggest employers.
OL,15,FHe remembers a time when thousands of
OL,16,Fpeople walked through the town to work
OL,17,Fevery day.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/19
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,310,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30905
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F309A1776708665
OL,3,CWill Labour lose its grip on power in
OL,4,Cthe Welsh election?
OL,6,F"In the morning in Maesteg in the 80s,
OL,7,Fyou'd see loads of people walking to
OL,8,Fwork," he said. "Come now, you won't
OL,9,Fsee anybody."
OL,11,FThe site has lay dormant for decades,
OL,12,Fbut will soon be used for housing.
OL,14,FJones, who joined the party in 1968,
OL,15,Fbelieves the long economic aftershock
OL,16,Fof industrial decline is now beginning
OL,17,Fto reshape politics in places that
OL,18,Fonce formed Labour's bedrock.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/19
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,310,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30906
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F309A1776708665
OL,3,CWill Labour lose its grip on power in
OL,4,Cthe Welsh election?
OL,6,F"The jobs are not here," he said,
OL,7,Fdescribing the daily stream of traffic
OL,8,Fnow leaving the valleys for work in
OL,9,FBridgend, Cardiff, Bristol, and
OL,10,Fbeyond. For him, the bigger question
OL,11,Fis what that means for the next
OL,12,Fgeneration.
OL,14,FParts of the valleys still rank among
OL,15,Fthe most deprived communities in
OL,16,FWestern Europe.
OL,18,FLiving standards remain stubbornly low
OL,19,Fdespite decades of regeneration
OL,20,Fefforts.
OL,26,@nD@AOUnD@XO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/19
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
