OL,3,CWill Labour lose its grip on power in
OL,4,Cthe Welsh election?
OL,6,FThat frustration is not unique to this
OL,7,Farea, and Labour would point to a
OL,8,Frecord in government that includes
OL,9,Ffree prescriptions, major transport
OL,10,Finvestment, and repeated attempts to
OL,11,Fprotect Welsh public services from
OL,12,Fwhat it calls the harshest effects of
OL,13,Fpost-2010 austerity.
OL,15,FBut after 26 years in power in Cardiff
OL,16,FBay, the party is also being judged on
OL,17,Fwhether life in communities like these
OL,18,Ffeels materially better.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/19
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
