CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F309A1776708665
OL,3,CWill Labour lose its grip on power in
OL,4,Cthe Welsh election?
OL,6,FWith an anti-incumbent mood being
OL,7,Fregistered across many democracies,
OL,8,FLabour is now facing a double whammy
OL,9,Fin Wales.
OL,11,FFor the first time since 2007, Welsh
OL,12,FLabour is carrying the weight not only
OL,13,Fof its own long record in Cardiff Bay,
OL,14,Fbut of frustration with a Labour
OL,15,Fgovernment in Westminster too.
OL,17,FFormer First Minister Carwyn Jones,
OL,18,Fwho led Welsh Labour for nearly a
OL,19,Fdecade, accepts the scale of the
OL,20,Fchallenge.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/19
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,310,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30910
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F309A1776708665
OL,3,CWill Labour lose its grip on power in
OL,4,Cthe Welsh election?
OL,6,F"In the polls of polls, they don't
OL,7,Flook brilliant at the moment," he told
OL,8,Fme. "Let's not pretend things are
OL,9,Fwhere we want them to be."
OL,11,F"We are fighting on more than one
OL,12,Ffront. Traditionally, it was us and
OL,13,Fthe Tories. Pretty much those days
OL,14,Fhave gone."
OL,16,FHis argument is that Labour's task is
OL,17,Fnow to restore belief that a better
OL,18,Ffuture is possible.
OL,26,@nD@AOUoD@^O]qD@ZO]sD@AOUvD@KO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/19
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,310,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30911
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F309A1776708665
OL,3,CWill Labour lose its grip on power in
OL,4,Cthe Welsh election?
OL,6,F"We know things are tough. They've
OL,7,Fbeen tough for a long time...but we
OL,8,Fhave a way out of this hole."
OL,10,F"I think you have to convince people
OL,11,Fthat there will be a better future
OL,12,Fbefore they actually see it," he said.
OL,14,FThat challenge is complicated by a
OL,15,Ffast-changing political landscape.
OL,17,FThe party is being squeezed between
OL,18,FPlaid Cymru on the left and Reform UK
OL,19,Fon the right.
OL,26,@nD@AOUpD@]O]rD@AOUtD@]O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G11/19
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,310,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30912
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F309A1776708665
OL,3,CWill Labour lose its grip on power in
OL,4,Cthe Welsh election?
OL,6,FThe new, proportional, Senedd voting
OL,7,Fsystem could also make it easier for
OL,8,Fvoters to back the party that best
OL,9,Freflects their frustrations without
OL,10,Ffeeling they are wasting their vote.
OL,12,FIn Tredegar, one man told me: "We're
OL,13,Flike sheep in the valleys, we're
OL,14,Falmost bred to vote Labour," adding
OL,15,Fthat younger people no longer seem to
OL,16,Fcarry the same instinctive loyalty.
OL,26,@tD@_OUvD@\O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G12/19
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
