PN,30915
SC,0015
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F309A1776708665
OL,3,CWill Labour lose its grip on power in
OL,4,Cthe Welsh election?
OL,6,F"What we are seeing now is a really
OL,7,Ffundamental unravelling of the bonds
OL,8,Fthat connected people with Welsh
OL,9,FLabour," she said when we spoke beside
OL,10,Fthe statue of Keir Hardie in Aberdare.
OL,12,FBut Professor McAllister is also
OL,13,Fcareful not to overstate the idea of
OL,14,Fan unbroken Labour loyalty in the
OL,15,Fvalleys.
OL,26,@nD@AOUqD@HO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G15/19
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,310,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30916
SC,0016
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F309A1776708665
OL,3,CWill Labour lose its grip on power in
OL,4,Cthe Welsh election?
OL,6,FFirst-past-the-post election results
OL,7,Fhave masked shifts that were already
OL,8,Ftaking place, she argues, with Plaid
OL,9,FCymru and parties like UKIP and now
OL,10,FReform having all shown strength
OL,11,Fbefore, while Labour continued to win
OL,12,Fseats.
OL,14,FWhat makes this moment different, she
OL,15,Fsays, is the timing: dissatisfaction
OL,16,Fwith Welsh Labour's record in Cardiff
OL,17,FBay colliding with frustration at a UK
OL,18,FLabour government in Westminster, all
OL,19,Fin a new proportional system where
OL,20,Fvoters may feel freer to break old
OL,21,Fhabits.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G16/19
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,310,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30917
SC,0017
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F309A1776708665
OL,3,CWill Labour lose its grip on power in
OL,4,Cthe Welsh election?
OL,6,F"It's the perfect storm, really," she
OL,7,Fsaid. "Both governments unpopular
OL,8,Fsimultaneously...and all of that has
OL,9,Fcome at a dreadful, dreadful time for
OL,10,FLabour in the run-up to the Senedd
OL,11,Felections."
OL,13,F"If that plays out in the way that it
OL,14,Fmight in May, then that's a huge
OL,15,Fpolitical earthquake."
